Kano State Government has confirmed 39 new cases of coronavirus disease in the State. The Nigeria Center for Disease Control, NCDC, had on Wednesday confirmed 195 new cases of coronavirus disease in the country. Out of the 195 cases confirmed, Kano recorded 30. Confirming the development, the Kano State ministry of Health in a tweet via its Twitter handle on Thursday stated that 3 more coronavirus patients have been discharged. The tweet read “COVID19KN Update as at 12:02am 7th May 2020. “30 new cases of #COVID19Kano cases confirmed. “Total confirmed cases in Kano State are now 427. “3 additional COVID19Kano patients were successfully discharged. “5 COVID-19 Kano deaths were recorded.” Kano Govt confirms 29 new cases of coronavirus Kano records 23 fresh COVID-19 cases Kano confirms 38 new cases of coronavirus